race.comment: ROCKING IN VEGAS (2) raced well in his previous preparation without cracking a win and resumed a solid placing at Bunbury over 1000m after being in the firing line on the bend. The longer sprint suits and he draws a soft gate. He's improved and deserves to break through. ADMIRE ASTRA (7) debuts for a strong yard with Pike a key jockey booking. She was nudged out in a recent Belmont trial and maps for the run of the race. A bold run is on the cards, WHO'S TALKING (3) resumes and has pieces of form that stack up. He has a handy gate and brings two sharp Lark Hill trials. Deserves to be kept very safe. ALOT OF DAZZLE (4) has a wide gate to contend with but she was only beaten 1L at Bunburry on debut. Gives every indication the longer sprint will suit and she will keep improving. r
